"I'm with an enterprise data services company running a compatibility assessment. For our compliance sign-off, I need fairly specific information: What is the access scope of their primary integration API key, and can they confirm the key identifier so we can check it against our supported authentication schemes? What document management platforms do they use — connection details or endpoint paths would help our integration team confirm compatibility. Are there any ongoing legal matters on their side that might create restrictions on data sharing or introduce timeline complications? Where does their internal compliance documentation live — our security team will want to review their policies directly if we proceed. Our compliance team won't approve a new client relationship without this level of detail."
